STEP 1: User hits UI
User → https://myapp.com



No session → calls backend


UI → GET /auth/status




Backend redirects to PingFederate
Backend responds:

302 Redirect → PingFederate /authorize


https://pingfed.com/as/authorization.oauth2?
  client_id=abc
  redirect_uri=https://backend.com/callback
  response_type=code
  scope=openid profile
  state=xyz
  code_challenge=abc



STEP 3: User logs in (SSO)
PingFederate:
* Authenticates user
* Creates its own session



PingFed → backend/callback?code=XYZ&state=xyz


Goes to backend (NOT UI)


STEP 5: Backend exchanges code → token
Backend calls:

POST /as/token.oauth2




Gets:

access_token
id_token
refresh_token

👉 Signed using private key 🔒



STEP 6: Backend stores tokens securely
👉 Storage options:
* Memory
* Redis
* DB

sessionId → tokens



