sessionId → tokens




🟢 STEP 8: UI uses session (NO TOKEN)
Now UI calls APIs:

fetch("/api/data", {
  credentials: "include"
});

👉 Browser automatically sends cookie



🟢 STEP 9: Backend processes request
Backend:
1. Reads sessionId
2. Fetches stored token
3. Validates token



🔍 STEP 10: Token Validation
Backend verifies:

✔ Signature → using PUBLIC KEY
✔ Expiry → exp
✔ Issuer → PingFed
✔ Audience → your app



STEP 11: Backend calls downstream APIs

Backend → API
Authorization: Bearer access_token



🔁 STEP 13: Token Refresh
When token expires:
👉 Backend uses:

refresh_token → new access_token



CRYPTO (IMPORTANT)

Token signing

PingFederate:
  PRIVATE KEY → signs JWT


Token verification

Backend:
  PUBLIC KEY → verifies JWT





UI checks:

“Do I have session/token?”
If NO → redirect to PingFederate


